    thinking: "**Defining App Scope**\n\nOkay, I\'m now zeroing in on defining the scope for this expansive Android application. The core focus is an AI-powered cleaning service booking platform. It will be a three-role-based system: Client, Worker, and Admin. Material Design 3, Jetpack Compose, and Kotlin are key tech components.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Core Features**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the features and aiming for a practical approach. It seems the best path is to build a single Jetpack Compose app, incorporating a role selector for Client, Worker, and Admin interfaces. While a complete UI is the goal, I will concentrate on the critical flows to ensure a manageable project scope. I plan to use Clean Architecture to create a solid foundation, which will include UI, Theme, and Navigation.\n\n\n**Refining UI Structure**\n\nI\'m now establishing the visual style, with Material Design 3 and a color scheme centered around blue (#2563EB), green (#10B981), and amber (#F59E0B). Thinking about user roles, a splash screen with role selection seems ideal or a simple auth flow. I will center the navigation around a central `AppNavigation` system for top-level auth and routing. I\'ll focus on a robust UI incorporating the components, building functional navigation and a beautiful MD3 themed UI for the Client, starting with core screens.\n\n\n**Implementing App Foundations**\n\nI\'m now focusing on setting up the fundamental structure and configuration. I\'ve started by updating `metadata.json` and `strings.xml` to reflect the \"CleanAI\" app name. I am also planning to change the package structure and `applicationId` in `build.gradle.kts`. After this, I need to ensure correct Material Design 3 application by reviewing `SKILL.md` before integrating Navigation Compose and the Theme. Finally, I will be building the authentication and client home flow.\n\n\n"
